<TITLE> Scholastica holds graduation ceremony </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 2 (bdnews24.com)  Scholastica, a leading English medium school, handed out certificates to its O-level graduates of 2006-07 at a glittering ceremony at its Uttara branch Friday. Students of different grades of the school threw an impressive cultural evening to celebrate the occasion. How popular Scholastica chairperson Yasmin Murshed is with her students became clear when she went onto the dais to address the audience. The hall erupted in applause and cheers when she spoke to her students making them have nostalgic reminiscences. Held equally in huge respect, Murshed spurred them on to work hard for the A-level that she said was the most important examination in their school days. Scores of teachers, students and guardians were enjoyed the colourful ceremony. bdnews24.co
